rooms...ENDORSEMENT...To the extent that the Government is requesting that a video monitor be provided in a counsel room at 40 Foley Square, the request is granted to the extent the District Executive can accommodate the request. If the Government is requesting a video monitor in its own offices, the request is denied.The request is granted as to defense counsel's room. SO ORDERED (Signed by Judge Alison J. Nathan on 11/22/21)(jw) (Entered: 11/22/2021)
11/22/2021 485 ORDER as to Ghislaine Maxwell. The Court is in receipt of the Government's proposed redactions to the parties supplemental briefing and the Court's Memorandum Opinion & Order regarding the admissibility of the anticipated testimony of Witness-3. Dkt. No. 481; see also Dkt. No. 477. Accordingly, the parties are ORDERED to file the redacted papers on the public docket by November 22, 2021, including the Government's supplemental letter regarding Witness-3 dated November 7, 2021 in response to Dkt. No. 417. The Court will file the redacted Memorandum Opinion & Order (Signed by Judge Alison J. Nathan on 11/22/21)(jw) (Entered: 11/22/2021)
